    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">BBQ Ribs</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 racks of baby back ribs</li>
            <li>1/4 cup brown sugar</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon smoked paprika</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon chili powder</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon garlic powder</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon onion powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cayenne pepper</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper to taste</li>
            <li>1 cup barbecue sauce</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>dinner</li>
            <li>barbecue</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 300°F (150°C).</li>
            <li>Remove the membrane from the back of the ribs and pat them dry with paper towels.</li>
            <li>In a bowl, combine brown sugar, smoked paprika, chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper to make the dry rub.</li>
            <li>Rub the dry rub all over the ribs, ensuring they are well coated.</li>
            <li>Wrap each rack of ribs tightly in aluminum foil and place them on a baking sheet.</li>
            <li>Bake in the preheated oven for 2.5 to 3 hours or until the ribs are tender.</li>
            <li>Preheat a grill or broiler. Unwrap the ribs and brush them with barbecue sauce.</li>
            <li>Grill or broil the ribs for a few minutes on each side until the sauce is caramelized and the ribs are slightly charred.</li>
            <li>Slice the BBQ Ribs and serve with additional barbecue sauce on the side.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious and smoky BBQ Ribs!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

